default&#xa0;default5. default              defaultSolutiondefault&#xa0;
defaultThe simplest and most robust solution to 
defaultthe above 
defaultproblems is to find a way to reliably and systematically 
defaultverify the age of Users when visiting certain websites and, at the same 
defaulttime, to protect their privacy.
default&#xa0;
defaultThis can be easily done using a unique code that is issued based on 
defaulta face
default-to-face and ID verification and then used regularly by Users when visiting c
defaultertain websites.
default&#xa0;
defaultWe are suggesting utilising the 
defaultPost Office’s 
defaultvast network of 
defaultbranches 
defaultacross the UK to verify the age of Users so Users can generate these unique codes automatically.
default&#xa0;
default6. default              defaultImplementationdefault&#xa0;
defaultWe have 
defaultdeveloped 
defaulta website that enables each 
defaultauthorised Post Office employee to verify the age of any User who presents a valid ID in person.  This verification enables the User to generate a unique Code online.
default&#xa0;
defaultIf the User would like to visit a third-party website that requires age verification, th
defaultey can enter this generated Code on that website. This Code will then be authenticated by our servers without revealing the name or details of the User as 
defaultwe don’t hold this information.
default&#xa0;
defaultTherefore, third-party websites will be able to grant access to real
default Users with the appropriate age, at the same time that the privacy of these Users will be protected.  Furthermore, for additional safety, Users (or their parents) will receive an email or an SMS notification each time the Code is used.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe Post Office can
default charge a fee for verifying the accounts of Users in a similar manner to how it processes passport applications.
